<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020-02-18</DATELINE><TITLE>We shouldn't worry when a virus mutates during disease outbreaks</TITLE><BODY>Mutation. The word naturally conjures fears of unexpected and freakish changes. Ill-informed discussions of mutations thrive during virus outbreaks, including the ongoing spread of SARS-CoV-2. In reality, mutations are a natural part of the virus life cycle and rarely impact outbreaks dramatically.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>